Six women in photo, but the fifth is labelled only with a &quot;?&quot;

Probably from the Long Island suffrage parade of 1913--here's mention from the New York Times report of 24 May:

&quot;Mrs. Sadie Keene represented the FIfteenth Assembly District of New York in the parade, and Miss Grace Collins marched as the Captain of a FIre Department, and Mrs. John Ocksbury as a drummer.&quot;

Olive Schultz was driver for the suffrage hike led by &quot;General&quot; Rosalie Jones, and later ran a taxi service for suffragists in New York (she split the fares with the Women's Political Union).
